window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Cruel. Coldblooded. Hades in a Brioni suit.</p> <p>Cillian Fitzpatrick has been dubbed every wicked thing on planet earth.</p> <p>To the media, he is The Villain.</p> <p>To me, he is the man who (reluctantly) saved my life.</p> <p>Now I need him to do me another small solid.</p> <p>Bail me out of the mess my husband got me into.</p> <p>What’s a hundred grand to one of the wealthiest men in America, anyway?</p> <p>Only Cillian doesn’t hand out free favors.</p> <p>The price for the money, it turns out, is my freedom.</p> <p>Now I’m the eldest Fitzpatrick brother’s little toy.&nbsp;</p> <p>To play, to mold, to break.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>Too bad Cillian forgot one tiny detail.</p> <p>Persephone wasn’t only the goddess of spring; she was also the queen of death.</p> <p>He thinks I’ll buckle under the weight of his mind games.</p> <p>He is about to find out the most lethal poison is also the sweetest.&nbsp;</p>"; 
